      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection is justified by comparison to PIV data; hemolysis model form is documented with literature support.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-ω turbulence model was selected based on prior published comparisons for rotating cardiovascular geometries. Hemolysis was computed via the Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law model, which is the most widely used model for CFD hemolysis assessment in the literature. Model form is considered appropriate for MRL 2. Required Level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
