    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. The six not-assessed factors are acceptable under MRL 2 scope. Validation evidence demonstrates R² = 0.923 for shear-stress magnitude and 4.4% relative error in RH at the nominal operating point, both meeting their respective acceptance criteria. The assessment team concluded that the CFD model has sufficient credibility to support the COU decision: identification of worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. The primary validation metric (pooled R² on scalar shear magnitude) was accepted as the principal evidence of hemolysis prediction fidelity, and the model is accepted for use.",
